column5: Please go to the Will Call Booth (not sure where it is) to pick up your tickets if ya won some.. Im trying to get ahold of the organizers.. I sent them the list yesterday but haven't heard back.. im assuming they got it.. Im on my way first thing in the morning hope to see some people there!!
Was there today... Go to hall 5 the booth is there... They had the info but were confused when I asked for free tickets from OFC lol
and here I thought I had a shot at winning a ticket
I'll be a gunin for ya, sheriff!
I will be there with my wife and our oldest tomorrow
The "Will Call" booth is just inside the main doors of building 5, just to the right of the ticket booths.
Boss, yer in for one hell of a drive. NASTY WIND.
Bah!!! Im from NORTHERN Ontario.. thats just a breezy spring morning!! I should be there around noonish!! Ta Ta
I hear parts of the 400 are closed
Thanks Terry, i see that, north of Barrie the map says... hopefully it will be open by the time we get there or we will just have to go around!!

Thanks again for the tickets TJ (and also Gerritt!).  They didn't have the info from you at the will call booth on Saturday, but there was no issue with giving me the tickets. My Wife and I went and met our Daughter and Son in Law too.  I enjoyed the show. I didn't see any great deals, but it was a nice way to spend the day anyways. The expanded area was sorta a flea market of ShamWow type stuff. Hopefully next year they can fill that section as well. The dog training was neat though and a nice addition.
